-- Same-store sales up 1.2 pct in February: ICSC
-- 
-- Thu Mar 6, 2008 3:42pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/06/us-usa-retailsales-icsc-idUSN0621105220080306

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Retailer sales rose 1.2 percent at stores open at least a year, the International Council of Shopping Centers said on Thursday. 

 The increase was above the council's forecast range of 0.5 percent to 1 percent, Michael Niemira, chief economist for the council, said during an interview. (Reporting by  Brad Dorfman , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)